@Sam-Kruglov I ran your test cases with on the latest main commit, both test don't show any stack trace.

The final assertion error thrown is `AssertJMultipleFailuresError` which aggregates all caught errors but don't show any the stack trace because it would clutter the overall error message (similar to opentest4j `MultipleFailuresError`).

Now the question is what would you like to see in the error message, a (partial?) stack trace per error or the current behavior?

@Lanninger08 let's see what is the real problem to solve, sorry your PR might not be relevant but thanks for it anyway.
